content.div:
"That sh*t cray."

It's the hook to Jay-Z and Kanye West's "N***as in Paris!"

The break-out catchphrase of 2011!

Three words capable of making your high school English teacher weep!

It's also a nonsensical yet succinct summary of the just-released clip for Watch the Throne's "N***as in Paris" -- directed by West himself, and filmed during the Watch the Throne tour's run through L.A. -- a kaleidoscopic take on a concert video that goes H.A.M. on anyone with epilepsy. (No joke. Please heed the health warning posted at the beginning of the clip -- especially if you're considering replaying it 11 times to relive the full live-show experience.)

As Billboard notes, the video comes 23 weeks after the Watch the Throne single first charted -- making its appearance today a little curious. That said, holograms of lions and panthers are always popular, no matter where they appear in an artist's promo schedule.

Watch "N***as in Paris" below:
